    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-08-06T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-08-06T06:00:00-05:00" n="852"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d852">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">683.84A322/8–654: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 852<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Israel (<persName corresp="#p_RFH1" type="from"
                            >Russell</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d852fn1">Repeated to London, Cairo, Jidda, Amman, Beirut,
                        Damascus, Baghdad, and Jerusalem.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-08-06T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 6, 1954—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>138. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 60.<note n="2" xml:id="d852fn2">
                        <ref target="#d850">Document 850</ref>.</note> My statement to <persName
                        corresp="#p_SM2">Sharett</persName> followed exactly <gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 41,<note n="3" xml:id="d852fn3">
                        <ref target="#d843">Document 843</ref>.</note> except for cryptographic
                    requirements.</p>
                <p>In addition to discussion reported <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss>
                        109,<note n="4" xml:id="d852fn4">Not printed.</note>
                    <persName corresp="#p_SM2">Sharett</persName> said he felt US could have made
                    simple request without detailing measures we would take in event of
                    non-compliance. I replied we attached great importance to efforts being made at
                    this time to make progress on some of Israel-Arab problems and felt it most
                    important there be no actions on either side which would have effect of stunning
                    them. I conjectured our disappointment at our lack of success when we made
                    simple request <gloss target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> not move Foreign Ministry to
                    Jerusalem (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 1399, March 4, 1953) and
                    again, when few weeks before Kibya, we expressed our deep concern at Israel’s
                    resumption of reprisal methods (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 154,
                    August 22, 1953) may have led Department to think <gloss target="#t_IG1"
                        >IG</gloss> would wish to understand full extent of our hopes for greater
                    success in capitalizing on present opportunity for improving situation.</p>
                <pb facs="1643" n="1603" xml:id="pg_1603"/>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_EAS1">Eban</persName>’s statement to Secretary may be way
                    of changing Prime Minister’s negative response to our request for further
                    temporary extension of demilitarized zone work stoppage, by saying <gloss
                        target="#t_IG1">IG</gloss> prepared hold up construction temporarily but not
                    permanently as it thought US had originally requested.<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d852fn5">
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFH1">Russell</persName> subsequently reported that in
                        a conversation on the evening of Aug. 6 with <persName corresp="#p_HCC1"
                            >Herzog</persName>, the Acting Head of the United States Division of the
                        Israeli Foreign Ministry, the Chargé referred to <persName corresp="#p_EAS1"
                            >Eban</persName>’s remarks to the Secretary (as reported in the
                        Department’s telegram 60 of Aug. 4). <persName corresp="#p_HCC1"
                            >Herzog</persName> said both he and <persName corresp="#p_SM2"
                            >Sharett</persName> understood the Department’s position perfectly and
                        the misunderstanding must have been <persName corresp="#p_EAS1"
                            >Eban</persName>’s. (Telegram 143 from Tel Aviv, Aug. 7, 2 p.m.;
                        683.84A322/8–754)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
